addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>An element <fr:tex>u</fr:tex> of a <fr:link
href="jms-001S.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-001S">pointed</fr:link> dpco <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is called <fr:em>positive</fr:em> when for any semidirected subset <fr:tex>I \subseteq  A</fr:tex>, if <fr:tex>u \sqsubseteq   \bigsqcup {I}</fr:tex> then <fr:tex>I</fr:tex> is inhabited. We will write <fr:tex>\mathsf { pos } \, {u}</fr:tex> to mean that <fr:tex>u</fr:tex> is a positive element.</fr:p><fr:p>(This is adapted from <fr:link
href="johnstone-1984.xml"
type="local"
addr="johnstone-1984">Johnstone</fr:link>’s definition of positive elements of frames to the case of dcpos by <fr:link
